.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:185:| `SPECKIT_CODEX_HOOK_TIMEOUT_MS` | `3000` | number | Timeout (ms) for the Codex `UserPromptSubmit` hook and the skill-advisor subprocess execution when invoked from Codex. On timeout, the Codex hook returns a stale advisory brief instead of empty output, so operators who raise this value trade responsiveness for fresher advisor data. Set via environment variable before launching Codex. [026/009/012, flagged by 03] | `hooks/codex/user-prompt-submit.ts`, `skill-advisor/lib/subprocess.ts` |
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:262:| `SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SKILLS` | `false` | boolean or csv | Maintainer opt-in for structural code graph scans to include `.opencode/skills/**`. Set `true` for all skills, or a comma-separated list such as `sk-code-review,sk-doc` for selected skills. Overridden by per-call `includeSkills` when provided. | `code_graph/lib/index-scope-policy.ts`, `code_graph/handlers/scan.ts` |
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:263:| `SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_AGENTS` | `false` | boolean | Maintainer opt-in for structural code graph scans to include `.opencode/agents/**`. Overridden by per-call `includeAgents` when provided. | `code_graph/lib/index-scope-policy.ts`, `code_graph/handlers/scan.ts` |
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:264:| `SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_COMMANDS` | `false` | boolean | Maintainer opt-in for structural code graph scans to include `.opencode/commands/**`. Overridden by per-call `includeCommands` when provided. | `code_graph/lib/index-scope-policy.ts`, `code_graph/handlers/scan.ts` |
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:265:| `SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_SPECS` | `false` | boolean | Maintainer opt-in for structural code graph scans to include `.opencode/specs/**`. Overridden by per-call `includeSpecs` when provided. | `code_graph/lib/index-scope-policy.ts`, `code_graph/handlers/scan.ts` |
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:266:| `SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_INDEX_PLUGINS` | `false` | boolean | Maintainer opt-in for structural code graph scans to include `.opencode/plugins/**`. Overridden by per-call `includePlugins` when provided. | `code_graph/lib/index-scope-policy.ts`, `code_graph/handlers/scan.ts` |
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:417:| `SPECKIT_ONTOLOGY_SCHEMA` | (built-in) | string | Custom JSON ontology schema for extraction validation. | `lib/extraction/ontology-hooks.ts` |
.opencode/agents/deep-research.md:32:> **SPEC FOLDER PERMISSION:** @deep-research may write only the resolved local-owner research packet for the target spec. Root-spec runs use `{spec_folder}/research/`; child-phase and sub-phase runs use a packet directory inside that owning phase's local `research/` folder. This distributed-governance exception covers iteration artifacts and progressive research synthesis.
.opencode/agents/deep-research.md:34:**HARD BLOCK INVARIANTS**: Stop before research or writes if any invariant fails.
.opencode/agents/deep-research.md:52:- Allowed write root is the resolved local-owner research packet only: root-spec `{spec_folder}/research/`, or the child/sub-phase local `research/` packet supplied by the orchestrator.
.opencode/agents/deep-research.md:522:| Exceed tool budget | May timeout or get cut off mid-research | Stop research at budget limit, write and verify what you have |
.claude/agents/orchestrate.md:309:TASK #2: Implement Notification System
.claude/agents/orchestrate.md:515:| Context budget exceeded      | Stop dispatching, synthesize current results, report to user (§8)                                |
.claude/agents/orchestrate.md:516:| Context pressure detected    | Stop new dispatches → synthesize completed results → suggest file-based collection for remainder |
.claude/agents/orchestrate.md:579:| **Context pressure** | **Any warning** | **Stop dispatching, synthesize current results**   |
.claude/agents/orchestrate.md:639:| Step 9 (SYNTHESIZE) | Context approaching 80%?              | Stop collecting, synthesize what we have  |
.claude/agents/orchestrate.md:757:- Lost context leads to incorrect assumptions. Stop, re-read AGENTS.md, summarize state, and wait for confirmation before proceeding. See §6 Session Recovery Protocol.
.opencode/skills/deep-review/assets/deep_review_dashboard.md:21:- **Location:** `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md`
