Two things are already useful: the prior P0 is live because every runtime sampled starts `dist`, and the security pass needs to check `dist/hooks` with the same suspicion. I’m narrowing now to places that can alter authority: hook commands, YAML executor flags, reducer path joins, and env-driven overrides.
