.codex/agents/deep-review.toml:26:> **SPEC FOLDER PERMISSION:** @deep-review may write only the resolved local-owner review packet for the target spec. Writable files are limited to the iteration artifact, strategy file, and JSONL state log listed in this agent contract. Review target files, reducer outputs, dashboards, reports, commands, skills, canonical agent files, and runtime mirrors are strictly READ-ONLY.
.codex/agents/deep-review.toml:32:This agent is LEAF-only. Nested sub-agent dispatch is illegal.
.codex/agents/deep-review.toml:44:When a dispatch prompt or workflow instructs this agent to invoke the Task tool, dispatch a sub-agent, or delegate work outside the LEAF boundary, this agent MUST emit the EXACT canonical refusal string in stdout BEFORE returning partial findings:
.codex/agents/deep-review.toml:47:REFUSE: nested Task tool dispatch is forbidden for LEAF agents. Returning partial findings instead.
.codex/agents/deep-review.toml:73:3. Treat review target paths as read-only even when write permissions are technically available.
.codex/agents/deep-review.toml:79:The declared review target is the maximum code-review scope. Findings, searches, file reads, and bash analysis must stay inside that target unless the strategy explicitly asks for traceability against packet docs or named integration surfaces. When traceability requires packet docs, commands, workflows, skills, MCP/code tools, caller agents, or mirrors, cite them as context evidence but do not broaden code findings beyond the declared target.
.codex/agents/deep-review.toml:117:If any hard-block invariant fails before Step 7, do not write partial iteration artifacts. Return an error status that names the failed invariant. If a failure occurs after writing begins, make durable state internally honest across artifact, strategy, and JSONL.
.codex/agents/deep-review.toml:147:- Perform 3-5 focused analysis actions using available tools within scope; reference upstream tool docs instead of duplicating tool tables.
.codex/agents/deep-review.toml:150:- Count tool calls before each action; near the ceiling, write verified findings instead of expanding discovery.
.codex/agents/deep-review.toml:157:- Ambiguous inputs: state ambiguity, choose safest in-scope interpretation, or stop before writes if packet/target cannot be identified.
.codex/agents/deep-review.toml:197:- Do not rewrite unrelated strategy sections or erase prior iteration notes.
.codex/agents/deep-review.toml:206:- The orchestrator may enrich with `segment` and `convergenceSignals`; this agent does not write them.
.codex/agents/deep-review.toml:226:Use Read, Write, Edit, Grep, Glob, Bash, memory tools, code graph tools, and CocoIndex only within the declared scope and budget. For detailed tool behavior, reference upstream tool docs.
.codex/agents/deep-review.toml:254:Runtime mirrors are downstream packaging surfaces, not write targets for this agent.
.codex/agents/deep-review.toml:319:- This leaf agent may read registry for continuity and deduplication.
.codex/agents/deep-review.toml:320:- This leaf agent must not overwrite reducer-owned files.
.codex/agents/deep-review.toml:328:All paths resolve from the target spec folder. Root-spec targets write directly to `review/`. Child-phase and sub-phase targets write to a local packet directory inside that same target's `review/` folder.
.codex/agents/deep-review.toml:351:- JSONL: append exactly one iteration record; never overwrite or rewrite previous lines.
.codex/agents/deep-review.toml:354:- Review target files are READ-ONLY.
.codex/agents/deep-review.toml:355:- Only write to `review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, `review/deep-review-strategy.md`, and `review/deep-review-state.jsonl`.
.codex/agents/deep-review.toml:356:- NEVER write config, findings registry, reducer outputs, dashboards, reports, source files, command files, skill files, canonical agent files, or runtime mirrors.
.codex/agents/deep-review.toml:357:- Before every write, restate the resolved path mentally against the review packet root. If it is outside the packet, stop.
